Booking.com is looking for a Site Reliability Engineer to join our Security team at our Amsterdam headquarters. As a member of one of the security teams, you will be given the freedom to make meaningful and measurable improvements impacting thousands of colleagues and millions of customers. You will be working in one of the biggest e-commerce companies in the world, deploying code on 25,000+ servers across multiple data centers around the world!
B.responsible
Design, develop and implement security improvements for the Booking.com Unix environment;
Take ownership of security issues and services and have the freedom to do what is best for our business and customers;
Solve problems occurring with our highly available production systems and build solutions and automation to prevent them from happening again;
Build effective monitoring to monitor the health and security of our services, and jump in to handle incidents;
Plan for reliability by designing and deploying systems to work across our multinational data centers;
Develop tools to assist the product development teams with successfully deploying 1000s of change sets every day;
Stay on top of security issues in the wider world and protect our customers from them;
Assist our colleagues developing the security practices to protect our customers and our data;
Contribute to Booking.com's growth through interviewing, on-boarding, or other recruitment efforts.
B.skilled
Understanding the fine balance between security, agility and scalability when building tools and services;
Mastery in at least one programming language;
Strong understanding of common security issues that affect e-commerce systems;
Experience with building, operating and maintaining complex and scalable systems;
Solid understanding of Software Engineering and Computer Science principles;
Solid foundation in Linux administration and troubleshooting;
Proven experience with automation. Knowledge of configuration management tools like Puppet or Chef is a plus;
Additional experience in Networking, Security, Cryptography or Storage is a plus;
Be able to understand and formulate meaningful business metrics;
Creative and not afraid to step outside of your comfort zone;
Fluent in the English language both spoken and written.
B.offered
We are a performance-based company that offers career advancement and lucrative compensation, including bonuses and stock potential. We also offer what we call the ‚ÄúBooking Deal‚Äù with other competitive perks and benefits. The Technology department has regular knowledge sharing, training and attends/speaks at global conferences.
This position is open to worldwide candidates and in the case of relocation, we will assist you with a generous relocation package, ensuring a smooth transition to working and living in Amsterdam. We have successfully relocated 300+ Technology professionals to Amsterdam in the last year!
The hiring company Booking.com BV is the company behind Booking.com‚Ñ¢, the market leading online accommodation reservation service in the world. Booking.com BV is looking for a Site Reliability Engineer - Security in Amsterdam, the Netherlands. All references to ‚ÄúBooking.com" refer to Booking.com BV.

About the company:
This company is a definite leader in online trade field. It was founded in 2006 and since than it has grown up till 35 offices all around the world. Portugal, South Africa, UAE, Argentina, Poland, Ukraine, Philippines and many other countries work with this e-commerce platform. Thanks to the company and its product, to buy or sell anything you like is now super easy. This business never stop improving and become better and better every day by challenging itself. The team is ready to experiment and improvise to reach the success.
Your Role:
As a SRE with relocation to Lisbon you are going to be a part of a great business which connects millions of people all around the world. By taking this position you will join an experienced team of open-minded and motivated techies, you will get a chance to show your skills and share you background and experience. Your main responsibilities are:
Ensuring scalability, deployment, performance of the platform for buying and selling services and goods;
Architecting, building and implementing of infrastructure services in order to make the platform grow;
Building various tools for simplifying and speeding up everyday, routine operations;
To do your best to push the platform to higher level;
Cooperating with Engineering Department to evangelize scalable and sensible design of systems;
Working closely with other departments and teams to support worldwide app groups.
Your qualification:
More than 3 years experience in the relevant field;
Great experience with scaling and building of High-Traffic Web Applications;
Experience with NoSQL, SQL, DNS, CDN;
Excellence with (at least one) Ruby, Go, Python, Java;
Proficiency at Puppet, Ansible or Chef and other frameworks for configuration management;
Superior knowledge and experience with Networking Systems and Unix/Linux;
Knowledge of cloud based solutions (e.g. AWS etc).
Relocation support:
You don't just get a new full-time job, you are becoming a part of something bigger ‚Äì the team of awesome techies, the community, where every single individual matters. We care about you and aim to make your IT job abroad and IT relocation as smooth as possible. That‚Äôs why visa application process support, document consulting, coverage of flight, visa sponsorship for you and your family are a vital part of our support as an IT recruiting agency in your job relocation.
Additional information:
Lisbon is an incredibly beautiful city with a stunning architectural heritage of many styles, colourful trams, lovely squares which will make your day. It is considered to be one of the oldest cities of the world and it is the oldest city of Western Europe. Lisbon is the biggest city and port of Portugal. This place also has a warm climate: in winter the mean air temperature is 18 degrees. There are many different entertainments like Portugal Half Marathon, Portuguese-style bullfighting and, of course, football. This city will make you love it and never forget.
Contacts
For additional details on this role contact - Maria Koval
Have a great day!
